column2: Several storms with heavy rains in previous two weeks- lake level high.
Many people on the lake during week of high temps.- lake level nearer normal.
Lily pads and other weeds that had been at or near the surface are dying back- algae gone from near shorelines.
Most surface weeds are gone- heavy rains on 9/12.
Heavy winds yesterday and this morning- lots of sediment stirred up.
Weather sunny and mid 60's- some wind earlier in the day.
A warm day with mild breezes- weird clumps- yellow/orange/green algae along lake shores-mostly on the S and SE shores.
Temperature was 81 F at sample time- dead fish washing up on the shore- though lessening.
Ice off 2nd week in April- Chippewa River backed into lake and flushed it out.
Water is the clearest it has been in 3 years.
IF TP  more than 0.2 RUN AT HIGH LEVEL
IF TP  more than  0.2 RUN AT HIGH LEVEL
Too much debris from flooding. Water level: Up 3"
Debris in lake- still high from flooding.  Water level: Up 2'
Rainy- no pollen or algae floating.
Rainy- no pollen or algae floating.
Rainy- no pollen or algae floating.
Rainy- no pollen or algae floating.
Water monitors set in river and inlet.
Heavy rains starting- river is over flood control tubes- entering lake.  1' raise in lake per day.
Lake level is up 5'- lake water is brown.
Ice off 4/25/96- water level 1.5' high- partly cloudy (60 degrees)- water calm.
78 degrees- windy 10-15 mph.  Little algal blooms.  Little rain last 10 days.
Heavy overcast.  Algae clearing off (scum gone) .
Partly cloudy- temp. 59 degrees.  Ice went out at 9:00 A.M. this morning .  Took secchi reading at 1:00 P.M.
Clear sky- temp. 60 degrees.  Nice day- very little wind.
Considerable amount of pine pollen on lake surface- weed growth slightly behind last year at this time.
Very little algae- lake 6" below normal.
Water brown/green- 5-10 mph wind- temp. 90 degrees. Very little algal bloom.
Algae blooms- mostly clear- 80 degrees.  Little wind 5 mph.
79 degrees. Calm- green bloom- no scum on water.
Algae blooms about done.  72 degrees- partly cloudy.  5-10 mph winds.  Rained an inch last night.
67 degrees.  Clear and calm.  Algae bloom.  Heavy rains this past week.
The temperature 80 degrees.  Mostly clear- wind at 5 mph.  Algae disappearing.
Water is clearing up.  Windy and cloudy.  Some mist and sleet.  36 degrees.
Clear and calm warm for this time of year.
Light wind.  Partly cloudy lots of rain.
Wind 5-10 mph lots of rain the past week.  Cloudy.
Partly cloudy and calm.  80 degrees.  Algae thick.
Mostly clear and calm.  85 degrees.  Muggy.  Algae thick.
Mostly clear and calm.  Wind 5-10 mph.  Algae clearing.
Partly cloudy.  Wind 5-10 mph.  70 degrees.  Little algae.
Clear sky.  Wind 10 mph south.  Excellent clarity for this time of year.  Numerous ducks + geese.
The weather has been warm with clear skies.  Excellent reading for this time of year.
Weed growth less than usual for this time of year.
Clear + warm with more sunshine than normal.
Cloudy + little sunshine (rain is more than usual).  Lots of pollen in the air and on the lake (pine).
Over 6" rain in last 5 days (muggy).  Some algae.  Slight breeze.  Creek coming into lake is very murky.
Algae present - some floating weeds - weed growth at peak - sunny - warm 97 F.
More rain than normal.  80 F.  Slight breeze.
Little humid.  Sunny.  Green scum on water.  Little wind.
Showers past two days.  Windy.  Cool low 46 F high 63 F.
Less scum on top of water.  Some floating weeds.
Water starting to clear.  Lake turn-over.
Clear- calm.  Have had lots of rain.  Beautiful day.
Partly cloudy- little wind.  Humid and warm.  Pollen in water.
Light rain- misty.  Water dirty from rain.
Overcast- light wind. Cool.  Water very green- unusual summer.
Winds 15-25 mph.  Mostly sunny.  67 degrees F.  Water starting to clear.
Wind 0-5 mph- partly sunny. 62 degrees F.- lake has turned over.  Water clearing.
Ice out 4/16/2001.  High water.  Temp 60 F.  Heavy overcast.  Loons and ducks on lake.
Water looks good.  More ducks on lake.  Pleasant day.
Today mostly cloudy.  Lots of wind and rain.  Water high.  Not much sunshine.
Sunny.  Water starting to green up.  Little wind.
Partly cloudy.  Last 6 days very hot and humid.  Lake with green algae.  Little rainfall.
Partly cloudy.  Very warm.  Water high most of the summer.
Water has odor.  Green scum.  Partly cloudy.
Satellite.  Mostly fair.  Nice day.  Water very green.  Bloom at peak.
Beautiful day.  Warm.  Sunny.  Less green coloring in water.
Water clearing.  Lake turn over.  Clear and beautiful day.  Lots of ducks.
Cloudy- water is dirty- cool day- a number of ducks and geese on lake- and cool spring.
Mostly sunny- very good secchi reading- above normal rainfall- and cool spring.
Mostly sunny- water is a little green- nice day- temperature is 80 degrees- and the last two weeks were hot and dry.
Sunny- algae green.  It has been windy and rainy and a warm summer.
Partly cloudy.  2 pairs of loons on lake.  Water is getting near normal.  Very cool nights.
Mostly clear- temp 82 F- humid.  No wind.  Some algae.  Perfect day.  Rain past week.
Partly cloudy- temp 70 F.  Wind 5-9 mph.  More algae.  Cool day- 1/2" rain last week.
Sunny- temp 80 F.  Calm- beautiful.  Very little rainfall (1.2").  Extremely dry.  Hot month.
Clear- temp 78 F.  Calm- beautiful day.  No rain for past four days.  Cool fall.
Great day- mostly clear.  Wind 3 mph.  Lake looks clear.  Loons on lake.  Ducks on lake.
Beautiful day- mostly clear.  Water calm.  Lake quality looks great.  Trees assorted green colors.
Mostly cloudy - weather cool and rainy the past 2 weeks.
Mostly fair - wind 8 mph.  Warm weather has arrived.  Weed growth increasing.
Fair sky.  Calm- warm.  Water turning green.  Slight scum on lake.
Clear sky- calm- warm day.  Low humidity.  Green.  No scum on water.
Partly cloudy.  Wind 5 mph.  Temp 65 F.  Lots of rain past two days.  Cool weather.  Cold August.
Partly cloudy - wind 5-10 mph.  60 F temp.  Cool weather.  Few ducks.
Fair sky- clear.  Wind 3-5 mph.  Scum is clearing up. Water less green.  Leaves turning color.
Clear- calm- 65 F.  Water green.  No scum on water.  Leaves in full color.  Beautiful day.
clear sky-wind 5 mph-very nice day-secchi reading poor for this time of year
clear sky wind 5-10 mph rain every day this past week-lake water looks good
partly cloudy no wind rain last few days water looks good
partly cloudy-wind 5-10 mph humid day-water looks very clear
clear sky wind 3-5mph warm and humid water looks good
partly cloudy wind 10-15 mph humid warm day water looks good not much algae
mostly fair wind 0-10 mph Temp 80F nice day water getting green- low humidity
mostly clear wind 0-5 mph nice day temp 68F water green with some scum on top
partly cloudy wind 5-10 mph temp.69F water green and about normal as in the past
mostly cloudy-calm-cool day-lots of rain the last 3 days-thick scum

column1: the only weed we have is the currly pond weed
there was no fish kill due to hot weather or for any other reason

column2: 65 deg. Sunny- Light Breeze- Loons- Geese with young. Nice morning.
Sunny- 76 Deg- Light Breeze- Loons- Geese- Herons- Ducks present.

column1: Helped by my wife Robbie Swanson

column2: Sunny- Light Breeze- Water is Slightly Green- We saw Eagle- Osprey- Geese- Gulls- Blue Herron
Lake is very high- This was a spring of extended high water- water is still coming in but the lake is draining. We just got boats out in the last couple of days.
Sunny- Mostly calm- Lake is still high but is draining.

Lake Level has come down a little- I went down the creek that drains Amacoy to the Chippewa River to check for Beaver Dam blockages but found none. It appears that there is a problem with the tubes/gates. This will be corrected by the Township/County.

column1: We are seeing Eagles- Loons- Herrons- Osprey

column2: Lake level is about down to normal. Sunny- light breeze- 69 deg- water is light brown. Loons- eagles- osprey- herrons- geese deer. We havn't had any duck families for the last couple of years. We had a pair of otters earlier this month but they appear to have moved on.
Lake is lower now about normal. Loons- hearons- geese with young ones. We have not had any ducks for at least 2 years.
65Deg   Calm   Partly Cloudy   Loons- Eagles and young ones- Ospry- 2 Geese and 1 young one- mink- Herrons- We have not had any nesting ducks this year or last year-
Lake is going up due to rain. Eagles and their young- Hearons- a Mink- Deer- we have not seen any Loons recently
59 Deg- Calm- Sunny-  Eagles and their young- Ducks are ariving back- Geese are gathering- Humming bird young have left- deer
Sunny- Calm- 58Deg- Loons Eagles Ducks migrating
75 Deg Partly Cloudy to start- rain chased us in

column1: Deer- Eagles- Osprey- Herons- Geese- Ducks- Loons

column2: Eagles- Loons- Herons- A Mink- Muskrats- 78Deg- Partly Cloudy- Light Breeze
Deer- Eagles- Loons- Herons-  Sunny- Calm- Cool 53 Degrees
Sunny- Light Breeze- No Loons today- Most Hummingbirds have left- a few youngsters hanging around- Red Breasted Grossbeaks are gone- Orioles are mostly gone

column1: Thanks to my wife Robbie for helping me all year. Partly Sunny- Light Breeze- 73Deg.

column2: Loons are gone- Orioles are gone- Hummingbirds gone- Grossbeaks gone
Filtered sun- 70 deg- calm- ducks migrating- loons are back- muskies are spawning- saw a otter-
Sunny/Partly Sunny Light Breeze.   Loons- Eagles-Osprey Herrons
Mostly Sunny Calm- Loons Eagles- Herrons- Green Herrons
